I don't think you can use this as a general class as it stands. A previous PR changed it to be non general, it seems:
    @Override
    public long write(ByteBuffer[] srcs, int offset, int length) {
        int position = buf.position();
        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++) {
            ByteBuffer src = srcs[i].duplicate();
            if (i == 0) {
                src.position(src.position() + offset);
            }
            buf.put(src);
        }
        return buf.position() - position;
    }

